Rating: 4
When I got to the store - the halibut looked much fresher than the swordfish - so I substituted. Also, I made it in the broiler and doubled the sauce recipe because I didn't use oil and I was worried it would be a bit dry. It was delicious! I make fish dishes three times a week and this will be a regular addition for sure.

Rating: 3
This dish was pretty good overall, but not what I'd call a 4 fork rating. The swordfish was very good, though, and I will make that part of it again. I used regular Dijon mustard, I think it would be even better with the country-style. The vegetables were pretty good, but my family was not crazy about them, so I probably won't make them again, but it was nice for a change.

Rating: 4
This is a wonderful recipe for guests. Everything can be prepared hours ahead, and when the guests are there, it just takes about 10 to 15 minutes to grill the fish and fry the vegetables. It looks colorful and appealing because of the cherry tomatoes. If there's a no-fish-eater present (like my husband), the vegetables are delicious also with a pork chop or a chicken breast.

